Beltrán-Sánchez H(1), Andrade FC.

Author information:
(1)Center for Population and Development Studies, Harvard University, Cambridge, 
MA 02315, USA. beltrans@hsph.harvard.edu

OBJECTIVE: To estimate transition probabilities between disability states, total 
life expectancy, and the latter's decomposition into years spent disabled and 
disability-free by age, sex, and education among older adults in São Paulo, 
Brazil, and urban areas in Mexico.
METHODS: Applied a micro-simulation method (Interpolative Markov Chains) using 
longitudinal data.
