depending on the dose of electromagnetic radiation of various types].

[Article in Russian]

Babkina VV, Chernova GV, Allenova EA, Endebera OP, Naumkina EN.

Biological effects of exposure to red light (lambda = 660 +/- 10 nm) on the 
viability and morphophysiological characteristics of Drosophila melanogaster 
have been studied. The ability of this physical agent to modify these features 
is shown. The degree of expression and impact of biological effects depend on 
the dose, functional and genetic status of the organism. The study of the life 
