Using a survey to estimate health expectancy and quality-adjusted life 
expectancy to assess inequalities in health and quality of life.

Collins B(1).

Author information:
(1)University of Liverpool/NHS Wirral, Merseyside, UK. Brendan.collins@nhs.net

BACKGROUND: There has been a policy debate in the United Kingdom about moving 
beyond traditional measures of life expectancy and economic output to developing 
more meaningful ways of measuring national well-being.
